{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, the continuous sign language dataset also needs to consider sentence segmentation and grammar, and include relevant supplementary information.",
    "It is evident that the recognition accuracy, data set size, creation cost, and cost-effectiveness corresponding to each data set are different.",
    "Therefore, the absence of appropriate corpora and datasets impedes further in-depth exploration of sign language research.",
    "Sign language data collection can be categorized into two methods: contact and non-contact.",
    "Contact equipment was previously used for gesture recognition, with typical examples including data gloves [116][117][118], myoelectric signal armbands, inertial measurement units (IMU) [119], WiFi [120], radar, smartphones, Leap Motion controllers [121], and Kinect [122,123], etc."
  ]
}